## Secure Storage

```
REQUIRED for sensitive data:
  iOS:      Keychain (via expo-secure-store, flutter_secure_storage, or native Keychain API)
  Android:  EncryptedSharedPreferences or Keystore

Store in secure storage:
  - Auth tokens (JWT, refresh token)
  - API keys
  - Biometric credentials

Store in regular storage (AsyncStorage / SharedPreferences):
  - Theme preference
  - Initial setup completion flag
  - Non-sensitive settings
  - Cached non-sensitive data

NEVER store in regular storage:
  - Passwords
  - Tokens
  - Personal data (government IDs, sensitive identifiers)
```

