## Push Notifications (IF your app uses push notifications)

### Setup

```
1. Request push permission at an appropriate moment (on launch if push is core to the experience, or contextually when the user first encounters a feature that benefits from it)
2. Send device token to backend on authentication
3. Update device token on refresh (tokens can change)
4. Remove device token on session end
5. Handle multiple devices per user (store all active tokens)
```

### Handling

```
Foreground (app is open):
  - Prefer in-app UI over system notification for most cases. Exception: critical, safety, and time-sensitive alerts should use system notifications even in foreground.
  - Show in-app banner/toast instead
  - Update relevant UI (badge count, primary list for the notification type)

Background (app is in background):
  - System notification appears
  - Tapping notification -> open the relevant screen (deep link)

Killed (app not running):
  - System notification appears
  - Tapping notification -> launch app -> navigate to relevant screen
```

### Rules

- **Never spam notifications** - user can disable per-type in settings
- **Rich notifications** where supported (images, action buttons)
- **Group notifications** by type/source (avoid spamming users with individual items)
- **Badge count** on app icon matches pending items
- **Clear badge** when user opens the relevant section
- **Silent push** for background data sync (no user notification)
- **User preferences for notifications** in settings (per-type toggle)

