## Gestures & Touch

### Standard Gestures

**Principle:** Map gestures to actions consistently - the same gesture should mean the same thing across the entire app.

[REFERENCE] Common gesture-to-action mappings:

```
Tap:         Select, navigate, activate
Long press:  Context menu, multi-select mode, drag-to-arrange
Swipe right: Go back (iOS navigation standard)
Swipe left:  Reveal action buttons on list items (delete, archive)
Pull down:   Refresh list content
Pinch:       Zoom on images/maps
Double tap:  Zoom in on images, or contextual action
```

### Rules

- **Minimum touch target**: `[DEFAULT]` 44x44 points (iOS) / `[DEFAULT]` 48x48dp (Android)
- **Spacing between targets**: Minimum `[DEFAULT]` 8px to prevent mis-taps
- **Visual feedback on every tap**: highlight, ripple, opacity change (never feel unresponsive)
- **Haptic feedback** for important actions (destructive, confirmation, toggle)
- **Swipe actions must be discoverable** - show hint on first use or have an alternative button
- **Never rely solely on gestures** - always provide a visible button alternative

