## Performance

### App Launch

- **Cold start to interactive**: Target under `[DEFAULT]` 3 seconds. Heavy apps (Flutter/React Native with large bundles) on low-end devices may take longer - optimize progressively.
- **Splash screen** covers initialization (don't show blank screen)
- **Defer non-critical work**: load preferences immediately, fetch data after first paint
- **Pre-load critical data** during splash (permissions, frequently accessed context)

### Lists

- **Virtualized/recycled lists** for any list over 50 items (FlatList, RecyclerView, ListView.builder). Smaller static lists on capable devices are fine without virtualization.
- **Avoid rendering all items** at once for large lists (100+ items will jank)
- **Image caching** - download once, serve from cache forever (until cache eviction)
- **Placeholder images** while loading (blur hash or solid color)
- **Smooth 60fps scrolling** - no janky frames

### Images

- **Resize server-side** - never send full-resolution to mobile
- **Multiple resolutions**: thumbnail (list), medium (detail), full (zoom)
- **Lazy load** images below the fold
- **Cache aggressively** (disk cache + memory cache)
- **Progressive JPEG** for large images (loads blurry -> sharp)

### Memory

- **Release resources** when screens are not visible (unsubscribe, cancel requests)
- **Monitor memory usage** - alert thresholds depend on device tier and app type (image/video/map-heavy apps use more; set per your target devices)
- **Large images**: Stream from disk, don't hold all in memory
- **Pagination**: Don't accumulate all pages in memory; window the dataset

