## Platform-Specific UX

### iOS Conventions

- Tab bar at bottom, navigation bar at top
- Swipe from left edge = back navigation
- Large title in navigation bar (collapsible on scroll)
- Action sheets from bottom (not centered dialogs for actions)
- Haptic feedback on toggles, destructive actions
- SF Symbols for icons (or consistent alternative)

### Android Conventions

- Bottom navigation bar OR navigation drawer
- Material Design 3 components and motion
- FAB (Floating Action Button) for primary creation action
- Snackbar for non-blocking feedback (instead of toast)
- System back button/gesture works throughout
- Material You dynamic color (optional but modern)

### Rules

- **Follow platform conventions** - an iOS user expects iOS patterns, Android expects Android patterns
- **Cross-platform frameworks**: Use platform-adaptive components where possible (different look on iOS vs Android)
- **Never fight the platform** - if iOS does back-swipe, don't disable it; if Android has hardware back, support it
- **Test on BOTH platforms** if cross-platform - never release iOS-only tested builds to Android

